dismissalText.commentary: Karim Sadiq c †Umar Akmal b Shahid Afridi 40 (47b 2x4 2x6 67m) SR: 85.1

dismissalComment.html: sharp catch by Umar Akmal! Afridi fired that a bit quicker outside off, Sadiq tries to drove but gets a thin outside edge and the ball sits nicely behind Akmal's gloves, he didn't have much time to react

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Nabi run out (Younis Khan/Mohammad Hafeez) 37 (56b 0x4 2x6 75m) SR: 66.07

dismissalComment.html: a run-out halts what was shaping up to be a healthy stand, he clips it down towards midwicket and Nabi charges off is crease and has to turn back, he tries to make his ground at the bowler's end, he dives and the throw by Younis Khan is accurate to Hafeez and the third umpire confirms it

commentTextItems.html: in a day of reverse sweeps Misbah decides to finish things off with one, changes guard and plays a lap sweep past short third man

commentPostTextItems.html: The presentation is on. Afridi is the Man of the Match: "Good practice for the upcoming games. Dressing room atmosphere is perfect."

Nawroz Mangal (he's got the help of an interperter): "Performance was satisfactory. Unfortunately our batting wasn't great. If we play consistently against teams like Pakistan we will get better and do well in the World Cup qualifiers. I would like to thank the PCB and I would like the ICC to present us with more opportunities."

Misbah: "Happy to see the spirit of the Afghan team. They way they started, I was a bit surprised. When they played T20 in Pakistan they were exciting. We got in Shoaib Malik because he's another spin option and also a lower-order batter."
Thanks for your company today. There's the first ODI against England that begins on Monday. Look forward to seeing you then. Cheers!

End of match: Afghanistan may have been beaten comprehensively by seven wickets, but far from disgraced. In fact they were quite sprightly in the field even when the game was firmly with Pakistan. Hopefully this will be the start of many more games against the Full Members ie, the big teams. And Pakistan should continue to assist them in whichever way. Iqbal Sikander, the former Pakistan legspinner, is now their coach.
Pakistan pretty much played full strength today, though public opinion would say that they would be better off experimenting with a new guy like Hammad Azam instead of Shoaib Malik.

commentTextItems.html: short and he swivels and pulls hard but finds deep square leg
steers it straight to cover point
slower ball again and he opts not to bash it away, pushes it to the off side
slower ball down the leg side and wide called
he makes room to slam it past the off side but it's a slower ball and he just pats it away
bowls it shorter and he opens the face and steers it to third man
the field is up and Younis wants to get this done with, pitched up and swinging in and he stays at the crease and scoops it over mid-on
Shapoor was lucky to get his head out of the way! Misbah smacked a low full toss straight back towards the bowler, Shapoor just about evaded it and the ball went scorching to long-on
squeezes it in front of point
powers it down the ground but mid-off's deep enough to run across and stop it

straight six! Misbah stands at the crease and lofts through the line, Nabi does really well to even attempt a one-handed catch at the edge of the rope and he nearly cleans up an attendant near the sightscreen
Misbah sizes to blast that out of the ground but then changes his mind and defends as it was a slower delivery
fullish delivery on the off stump and he thuds it down the track, Shapoor's boot gets in the way
drives off the front foot but can't beat mid-off

commentPostTextItems.html: Omar: "I think Misbah should have sent Umar and Shoaib instead of himself and Younis. They didn't play the tests and are out of batting practice. But I still think this is the best line-up  for the 1st ODI against England."

commentTextItems.html: pushes a full delivery back to the bowler
gets across and pushes a full delivery to sweeper cover
keeps a touch low again, he pushes it down to cover point
full outside the off stump and he punches it down to long-off

commentPreTextItems.html: Hotak returns for a new spell

commentTextItems.html: flatter delivery and he punches it down to sweeper cover

dismissalComment.html: sharp catch by Umar Akmal! Afridi fired that a bit quicker outside off, Sadiq tries to drove but gets a thin outside edge and the ball sits nicely behind Akmal's gloves, he didn't have much time to react

dismissalText.commentary: Gulbadin Naib lbw b Shahid Afridi 7 (23b 1x4 0x6 15m) SR: 30.43

dismissalComment.html: Afridi gets his fourth! Tossed up on off and it's a googly, Naib is forward and the ball strikes him  in front of middle, Taufel raises the finger

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Nabi run out (Younis Khan/Mohammad Hafeez) 37 (56b 0x4 2x6 75m) SR: 66.07

dismissalComment.html: a run-out halts what was shaping up to be a healthy stand, he clips it down towards midwicket and Nabi charges off is crease and has to turn back, he tries to make his ground at the bowler's end, he dives and the throw by Younis Khan is accurate to Hafeez and the third umpire confirms it

dismissalText.commentary: Mirwais Ashraf lbw b Shahid Afridi 12 (27b 2x4 0x6 26m) SR: 44.44

dismissalComment.html: yet another five-for for Afridi! The sharp googly is too good for Ashraf, jags back in from wide outside off and catches Ashraf flush on the pad in front of the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Dawlat Zadran b Wahab Riaz 12 (19b 0x4 1x6 20m) SR: 63.15

dismissalComment.html: the middle stump goes for a toss! Zadran stands wide outside the leg stump to give himself room, Riaz gets some reverse swing and beats the bat, the stump goes back a few yards

headshotImage.caption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Samiullah Shinwari lbw b Umar Gul 32 (68b 4x4 0x6 98m) SR: 47.05

dismissalComment.html: Shenwari tries to get very innovative and moves right across his stumps and tries to paddle a full toss wide of short fine leg, the ball clips his pads in front of the stumps, he appears to show his bat to the umpire but Taufel was convinced the ball snuck past the bat

dismissalText.commentary: Amir Hamza c †Umar Akmal b Wahab Riaz 0 (6b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: this time Akmal gets his man! Hotak chips down the track and gets an outside edge on the drive, Akmal takes the low catch and basically pleads with the umpire but he didn't have to wait too long for the umpire's decision

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez b Dawlat Zadran 8 (17b 1x4 0x6 17m) SR: 47.05

dismissalComment.html: played on! Thus time Dawlat brings the ball back in and cramps him for room, the ball was a touch quicker too and Hafeez was trapped at the crease trying to fend it off, inside edge onto the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Imran Farhat c & b Samiullah Shinwari 52 (67b 9x4 0x6 95m) SR: 77.61

dismissalComment.html: soft dismissal! Shenwari dropped the leg break a bit short, Farhat rocked back, showed the full face of the bat and spooned it back to the bowler, easy catch
